  "measurement_note": "Size is N, the garden length; D, the inclusive bloom-day range; and U, the number of distinct bloom days. The legal 8/32/128 tiers span 16x, permute every day from 1 through N, and require all flowers in N/2 adjacent pairs, forcing the answer to day N. Binary search with a linear feasibility scan takes O(N log D) time. A correct implementation that tests the U distinct bloom days in order takes O(NU), completes normally at N = 128, and is rejected by scaling.",
